<br>
1) Yes, I left the Federation boards. I got the sincere impression I wasn't welcome because I wasn't a Federation member. The feeling I got was 'join a federation guild or get out.' .. And that is the Federation's right to say. I'll still help people out if I get asked (feel free to email me or send me a tell in game) but I won't spam the Federation boards.<br>
<br>
My feeling was also that I was creating more trouble than I could possible be worth. Because of me a very nasty thread generated on the previous to that, very friendly and welcoming Federation board. When I posted a second thread, it became clear to me that the nastiness and distruptiveness would continue if I stayed.. and I really didn't want that. The world has enough crap without bringing it places with you. <br>
<br>
2) I did ask Lach to remove that nasty thread with all the mud slinging. I don't recall asking anyone to remove the second one, but I'm not protesting that it was. It was filled with a whole heck of a lot of nastiness, and people shouldn't have to read that.<br>
<br>
3) I can see how my second thread may have upset people.. the only reason I posted it was because I thought I had been asked a question. So, I had thought I would do my best to answer the question since I had been asked. I spent a long time considering my words and carefully weighing them so I wouldn't be saying bad things about anyone but at worst, myself. That the question asker was being sarcastic, facetious or rhetorical when they posted escaped me at the time. <br>
<br>
That aside, I want to say thank you to Bendi. In a week of my inbox being filled with nastiness, message boards I no longer visit (Not Federation) filled with venom, with people I thought were friends turning their back on me, people reading what they want to read, not what's written and being judged by people I've never even talked to, her words have been a shining beacon in the darkness. Bendi, you are a credit to Legion of Little Folk.. you embody what I think LoLF is all about. (I could be wrong. ^_^ ) .. Friendly, caring, willing to see the person behind the Toon and willing to stand up and voice her opinion. Thank you.<br>
<br>
<br>
